Question: How do you believe ACME should better support organizations and cultural leaders?

Response ID: resp_3829
Response Text: There are few spaces where local emerging artists can showcase their talent to a broad audience. The few big venues we have are mostly used by big out-of-town shows who can pay the astronomical fees they charge for space. They are inaccessible to many local groups. Venues are also concentrated downtown, which makes it hard for anyone living above University or below South Congress to access them without a car. Public transportation for them is unreliable and slow. 

I grew up in Bogotá, Colombia, where the arts are heavily funded by public funds and where there are an abundance of venues, great public transportation to and from, and many festivals that showcase prominent artists alongside emerging acts. I would love to see more venues of all sizes far north and south, where artists of every caliber can be appreciated.

